body:
## 🐛 Bug Report

It is setting border styles in random (sometimes adjacent) cells

When I set the border property for example to top: 'thin' it sets the border property actually in the top, but in a lot of cells I didn't specify.

![image](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/assets/97958821/13205666-2e42-4ff4-a84f-d5c7273a9816)
This is an example of when I try to set border around R5.


Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
await workbook.xlsx.readFile(template_file);
const ws = workbook.getWorksheet('XYZ');

ws.getCell('A1').border = {
  top: {style:'thin'},
  left: {style:'thin'},
  bottom: {style:'thin'},
  right: {style:'thin'}
};

ws.getCell(18, 5).border = {
  top: {style:'thin'},
  left: {style:'thin'},
  bottom: {style:'thin'},
  right: {style:'thin'}
};
```

## The expected behaviour:

Cell A1 bordered around

Cell R5 bordered around
